e\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering endpoint testing**\\n\\nI’m thinking about testing if the endpoint returns a Greeting record. However, if I'm checking the Springdoc documentation, it might be worthwhile to call the endpoint as well to exercise the real controller. Spring Boot uses Jackson for metadata reflection, so a record should be fine. But I wonder if a simpler endpoint returning a String would make things easier since OpenAPI would return the schema type as a string, which seems more straightforward. This might avoid complications with the Jackson model.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_lYwuWpWksP6BzZZ9C76SN9m0|fc_03bc5e692b8fbb93016a40230c970c8190b9d395e82b6fea50", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src -path '*/src/test/java/*Test.java' | head -20 | xargs -r grep -l \"SpringApplication.run\" | head -10"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 625, "output": 1352, "cacheRead": 13312, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 15289, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782588153965, "responseId": "resp_03bc5e692b8fbb93016a4022fa6aa08190a786a214865f97c7"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_lYwuWpWksP6BzZZ9C76SN9m0|fc_03bc5e692b8fbb93016a40230c970c8190b9d395e82b6fea50", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "(no output)"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1782588172922}]}
